<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFEFFBFFC959EC36D137E1D" pageId="19" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFEFFBFFC959EC36A987FBF" blockId="19.[831,1437,647,892]" pageId="19" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFEFFBFFC959EC36ABD7FFE" bold="true" box="[831,944,647,671]" pageId="19" pageNumber="33">Remarks:</emphasis>
It is characterized by longitudinal costae with slight extinctions and decreasing in chamber size toward the end.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFEFFBFFC959EA16D137E1D" blockId="19.[831,1437,647,892]" pageId="19" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFEFFBFFC959EA16D797F9F" bold="true" box="[831,1140,741,766]" pageId="19" pageNumber="33">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded in Midway fauna (Paleocene) by BERGGREN &amp; AUBERT (1975) and in the Late Paleocene by ANAN &amp; HEWAIDY (1986). It is recorded in the Maastrichtian and Paleocene zones of the Esh El Mallaha area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
